textline.data: From a security perspective, we assume that
persons of the system do not exchange the code
they know to request the cockpit door opening
We assume that there is at least one person aboard
It is not possible to enter in the cockpit by another way
than the door
The system must ensure that messages sent
by the Keyboard to the door system are authentic
The system shall ensure that an attacker
caprtuing data on the link between the keyboard
and the door system can not retrieve
the secret code
The button shall have a default position (norm),
an unlock position, and a lock position.
Once release, the button shall come automatically
come back to the norm position.
The system shall manage access to a cockpit.
The system shall provide crew
members with a phone line
connected to the pilot.
The system shall enable crew
members to contact the pilot.
The pilot shall unlock the
cockpit using a button..
The cocpit is initially
unlocked and empty.
The cocpit is initially
unlocked and empty.
The system shall allow crew members
to unlock the door using a dial pad.
The system shall allow the
pilot to unlock the cockpit.
The system shall allow the pilot to deny access
by maintaing the cockpit door locked for 5 minutes
before a new request can be performed
When the right code has been entered,
a buzzer rings and an open signal is
displayed just next to the door button
to invite the pilot to unlock the door.
